biogHists.text: Hannah Warrington Buzby was a New Jersey Quaker born on the 18th of the 11th month 1734, to Henry Warrington. Joseph Buzby was her spouse; the couple did not have any children. Buzby died in 1819 aged about 85 years due to a fit of coughing and spitting of blood which led to a broken blood vessel.

relations.note: Hannah Warrington Buzby was the sister of Elizabeth Warrington Haines Evans, spouse of Enoch Evans.
Hannah Warrington Buzby was the sister of Sarah Warrington, first spouse of William Rogers.
Hannah Warrington Buzby was the sister of Joseph Warrington, spouse of Rebecca Walton Warrington
Hannah Warrington Buzby was the sister of Rachel Warrington, spouse of Aaron Wills.
Hannah Warrington Buzby was the sister of Elizabeth Warrington Haines Evans, mother of Hannah Haines Thornton Yarnall.

resource.title: John Hunt papers, 1770-1828.
resource.abstract: John Hunt kept a diary for more than 40 years, recording Quaker concerns and daily events. This collections consists primarily of the manuscript journal, 1770-1800; fragments of 1805, 1806 & 1808; and 1814-1824. Of particular interest are the visits of prominent Quakers, including Elias Hicks and Jonathan Evans. There is also an account book, some correspondence received, and other miscellaneous materials. Correspondents include Ann R. Matlack, Asa Matlack, Elizabeth A. Lippincott, John Cox, Joseph Foulke, and Josiah Roberts.
